article: bosnia and herzegovina has formally agreed to send a contingent of soldiers to afghanistan as part of the international security assistance force -lrb- isaf -rrb- , yet a deadlocked collective presidency is keeping troops from this balkan country at home , nebojsa radmanovic , the serb member of the collective presidency , told reporters on monday .
